Genitalia (
Figs 22I , J
): Pygofer black dorsally, dark reddish-brown laterally; upper lobes in ventral view slightly undulating, with terminals directed inwards and tapering broadly; basal lobes in ventral view relatively linear, flat, in lateral view small, rounded and bulbous; median lobe of uncus rounded, exhibiting limited protrusion; claspers in ventral view conspicuous, diverging from point of downward deflection, with relatively narrow apices; pseudoparameres projecting further (ventrally) than endotheca and ventral support; ventral support acute, projecting slightly beyond endotheca; endotheca partially sclerotised.
